data.title: SÃO TOMÉ AND PRÍNCIPE Definition & Meaning
data.meta_description: São Tomé and Príncipe definition: a republic in western Africa, comprising the islands of São Tomé  and Príncipe,  in the Gulf of Guinea, north of the equator: a former overseas province of Portugal; gained independence in 1975. 372 sq. mi. (964 sq. km). Capital. See examples of SÃO TOMÉ AND PRÍNCIPE used in a sentence.
